Variation.
All six paratypes match the overall characters of the holotype (for measurements of the type series see 
Table 3
). All type specimens possess a dull white venter scattered with distinct dark blotches and marbling except that the dark patterns on venter is somewhat indistinct in the smallest male paratype, SYS a004597 (
Fig. 6
). No significant differences between males and females were revealed (
Fig. 5
), however females are slightly larger than males (SVL 28.8–28.9 mm in females versus 23.8–26.0 mm in males).
